The `init_non_singlecopy_gene_hmm_sources` function in the annotation database super-class is not keeping track of unique identifiers per hmm hit while it constructs the `hmm_searches_dict`.

Because `hmm_searches_dict` looks like this without any info about which hmm hits go together, it becomes impossible at the client side to take this information into account:

``` python
{
  "204_10M_MERGED.PERFECT.gz.keep_contig_1720_split_00013": {
    "hmms_testhmmcollection": [
      "ABC_tran"
    ]
  },
  "204_10M_MERGED.PERFECT.gz.keep_contig_1720_split_00014": {
    "hmms_testhmmcollection": [
      "ABC_tran"
    ]
  },
  "204_10M_MERGED.PERFECT.gz.keep_contig_1720_split_00015": {
    "hmms_testhmmcollection": [
      "ABC_tran",
      "ABC_tran"
    ]
  },
  "204_10M_MERGED.PERFECT.gz.keep_contig_1720_split_00016": {
    "hmms_testhmmcollection": [
      "ABC_tran"
    ]
  },
